Convert a Scott-encoded value to Church encoding (fold).

A type descriptor is a Scott list of constructor specs.
Each spec is a Scott list of fields.
Each field (Î»x.x) marks a recursive position.
In Haskell notation:
  data Bit  = O | I             is [[],[]]
  data Nat  = Z | S Nat         is [[],[âŠ¤]]
  data Bin  = E | O Bin | I Bin is [[],[âŠ¤],[âŠ¤]]
  data Pair = A | B Pair Pair   is [[],[âŠ¤,âŠ¤]]
Nat encodes as:
  Î»c.Î»n.c(Î»c.Î»n.n,
    Î»c.Î»n.c(Î»c.Î»n.c(Î»x.x, Î»c.Î»n.n),
    Î»c.Î»n.n))

A Scott value selects the ith of N case-handlers,
applied to its fields:
  Nat Z:    Î»z.Î»s.z
  Nat S(n): Î»n.Î»z.Î»s.s(n)

A Church value folds recursive fields by applying
them to all case-handlers:
  Nat Z:       Î»z.Î»s.z
  Nat S(S(Z)): Î»z.Î»s.s(s(z))

